                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13039923" author="pedrosans" created="Thu, 26 May 2011 21:03:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Quickstart reproducing the problem&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13039925" author="pedrosans" created="Thu, 26 May 2011 21:04:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;possible fix&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13039935" author="pedrosans" created="Thu, 26 May 2011 21:15:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;@devs, I think AbstractSingleSelectChoice needs to tweak the input to be understood by convertes ( my last patch ). I&apos;m just not sure if this is a good idea, because we can&apos;t know for sure who will parse the input since one can override the FormComponent#convertInput method.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13040059" author="ivaynberg" created="Fri, 27 May 2011 05:04:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;hrm. what is the usecase for setting a type on a choice component? like you have mentioned - there is no type converstion that is happening here, instead it uses a simple lookup from choice renderer. if anything, we should make calling settype() on it throw an exception.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13040087" author="ivaynberg" created="Fri, 27 May 2011 06:41:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;thought about it some more. the only clear way i see to make this better is to make settype() throw an exception when called on a component that uses an ichoicerenderer.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
